### HYMN XXVIII

#### A prayer to Agni for the destruction of evil spirits

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0102801">1</span></span>God Agni
hath come forth to us, fiend-slayer, chaser of disease,  
  Burning the Yātudhānas up, Kimidins, and deceitful ones.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0102802">2</span></span>Consume the
Yātudhānas, God! meet the Kimidins with thy  
   flame:  
  Burn up the Yātudhānis as they face thee, thou whose path is  
   black!  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0102803">3</span></span>She who hath
cursed us with a curse, or hath conceived a  
   murderous sin;  
  Or seized our son to take his blood, let her devour the child  
   she bare.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0102804">4</span></span>Let her, the
Yātudhāni eat son, sister, and her daughter's.  
   child.  
  Now let the twain by turns destroy the wild-haired Yātudhānis-  
   and crush down Arāyis to the earth!

